     1	# EDEN Roadmap
     2	
     3	Incremental build-up from empty repo to a complete EDEN protocol
     4	specification, reference implementation, and conformance suite.
     5	
     6	## Two orthogonal concepts
     7	
     8	- **Units** — the fine-grained decomposition. Each unit is a distinct,
     9	  named piece of work with its own exit criterion. Units are the
    10	  progress-tracking granularity: a unit can be crossed off even when it
    11	  ships in a shared commit with siblings.
    12	- **Chunks** — execution grouping. Units that must be designed and
    13	  implemented together (cross-referencing spec chapters, protocol
    14	  alongside its first consumer, shared commit-sized work) travel as one
    15	  chunk. Chunks are the review/commit granularity.
    16	
    17	**Rule:** a chunk can span multiple units; no unit spans chunks. If
    18	implementation runs over context mid-chunk, stop at the next unit
    19	boundary — never mid-unit. That keeps handoffs, resumes, and partial
    20	progress legible across sessions.
    21	
    22	Each phase also has explicit **non-goals** to prevent creep.
    23	
    24	---
    25	
    26	## Phase 0 — Bootstrap
    27	
    28	Repo shape, documentation shell, CI, GitHub hygiene. No runnable code
    29	and no spec content.
    30	
    31	**Units:**
    32	
    33	- **0a** — Repo scaffold (directory tree + section READMEs + root docs +
    34	  CI workflow + `.gitignore` + `.markdownlint.json` + `CLAUDE.md`
    35	  symlink). First `main` commit on GitHub; branch protection requiring
    36	  `docs-lint`.
    37	
    38	**Chunk:** 0a is one chunk — this bootstrap.
    39	
    40	**Non-goals:** any spec chapter content; any JSON Schema files; any
    41	Python; any reference code; any conformance scenarios.
    42	
    43	**Exit:** `docs-lint` CI job green on `main`; protected branch in place;
    44	all root and section READMEs accurately describe what's in the repo and
    45	what's next.
    46	
    47	---
    48	
    49	## Phase 1 — Spec v0 core concepts + schemas + fixture migration
    50	
    51	Writes the first normative chapters and the JSON Schemas they describe.
    52	
    53	**Units:**
    54	
    55	- **1a** — `spec/v0/00-overview.md`, `01-concepts.md`,
    56	  `02-data-model.md` prose. Defines experiment, trial, proposal, role,
    57	  artifact, metric, worker.
    58	- **1b** — JSON Schemas for config, task, event, proposal, trial,
    59	  metrics-meta under `spec/v0/schemas/`. Each cited from the data-model
    60	  chapter.
    61	- **1c** — Migrate `tests/fixtures/experiment/.eden/config.yaml` from
    62	  direvo; assert `experiment-config.schema.json` validates it. Add a
    63	  `schema-validity` CI job.
    64	
    65	**Chunk:** 1a + 1b + 1c — one chunk. Prose, schemas, and fixture
    66	cross-constrain each other; splitting would produce inconsistency.
    67	
    68	**Non-goals:** role contracts (Phase 2); event/integrator/storage
    69	chapters (Phase 4); any Pydantic code (Phase 3).
    70	
    71	**Exit:** schemas validate the fixture; `schema-validity` CI green;
    72	`02-data-model.md` cross-references all six schemas.
    73	
    74	---
    75	
    76	## Phase 2 — Spec v0 role contracts + task protocol
    77	
    78	Two more chapters. Defines what each role does and the task lifecycle
    79	they operate against.
    80	
    81	**Units:**
    82	
    83	- **2a** — `03-roles.md`. Planner, implementer, evaluator contracts:
    84	  discovery, claiming, context reading, execution, submission, release.
    85	  Per-role outputs and their expected schema shapes.
    86	- **2b** — `04-task-protocol.md`. Full task state machine (legal and
    87	  illegal transitions enumerated), claim-token semantics, submit
    88	  idempotency rule, wire format for task objects.
    89	
    90	**Chunk:** 2a + 2b — one chunk. Role contracts reference task
    91	lifecycle and vice versa.
    92	
    93	**Non-goals:** event protocol (Phase 4); any implementation (Phase 5+).
    94	
    95	**Exit:** state machine is pinned; `04-task-protocol.md` enumerates
